com.ti.debug.engine.scripting

Class Breakpoint

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ti.debug.engine.scripting.Breakpoint

  • public class Breakpoint
extends java.lang.Object
    This class encapsulates the breakpoint management methods. An instance of this class is automatically created when a new session is opened.

    Note: When specifying file paths during function calls, the slashes need to be represented using '/' or '\\' (with an escape character).

    // Create Environment and open a debug session
    ScriptingEnvironment env = new ScriptingEnvironment();
    DebugServer myServer = (DebugServer) env.getServer("DebugServer.1");
    DebugSession mySession = myServer.openSession("*", "*");

    ...

    // Add a breakpoint at a file
    int startBP = mySession.breakpoint.add("myFile.c", 15);
    int endBP = mySession.breakpoint.add("myFile.c", 22);

    ...

    // Remove a breakpoint
    mySession.breakpoint.remove(startBP);

      • removeAll

        public void removeAll()
               throws ScriptingException
        Remove all user-created breakpoints. This includes breakpoints that were loaded via an XML config file or created outside the context of Debug Server Scripting (i.e. If using DSS via the CCS script-console, this method will remove breakpoints created via the breakpoint user-interface)
        Throws:
        ScriptingException - if a breakpoint could not be disabled prior to removing it.
